-Principles of Rest Assured
    Follows a BDD approach
    Given- Prepare a request
    When- Make the request
    Then- performs assertions/ verifications
    can also use words like And depending on the

Hamcrest Matchers?
 JsonPath vs jsonPath()

 JsonPath is a class

 jsonPath() is a method that belongs to JsonPath class

 Cucumber scenarios - describe business rules/ requirements or the behavior that user will take on an application

 Example: Given a user is on the home page, When the user logs in, Then the user sees landing page

